dding-left:4.75pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ublic providers of NHS services, particularly foundation trusts, want to take responsibility for creating </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">services that are clinically and financially sustainable over the long term</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">progress </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">they have made </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">over the last two years i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n delivering </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">year-on-year efficiency savings to improve the value</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">-for-money of patient services</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is an illustration of this commitment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">efficiency gains </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">required</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to meet the ‘extended’ Nicholson Challenge</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> are not deliverable without transformational change</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to how </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'