<span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">fund new integrated models of care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Either way</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> we </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">see little prospect</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of ITF-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">funded</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> activity delivering</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> immediate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> compensating benefit to cover the loss of such a significant amount of NHS funding</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Additionally, while</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the evidence for improved clinical </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">outcomes from integrated out of hospital services is strong, there is much weaker evidence that such services deliver significant efficiency savings</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Therefore,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the ITF is likely to translate into an extra funding cut for the NHS</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Chief Executive of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">NHS Eng</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">land, for example, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">old CCGs in a letter on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">10</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> October</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that the ITF “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">will require the NHS to make savings of over £2 billion in existing spending…This implies an extra productivity gain of 2-3% across the NHS as a whole in 15/16</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">We will work wit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">h Monitor to determine how this is reflected in the expectations placed on…providers in the form of the efficiency deflator incorporated in tariff”</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">His Finance Director </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">stated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> at an NHS England Board meeting in the summer that: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“this is not just a small</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> adjustment to the percentage savings that need to be done, that takes it into a whole different category of the stretch that is required</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">It's quite a heroic undertaking”</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The FTN would go further and say that, at this point, it is impossible to see </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">how such savings</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> – between 6 and 8% </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">annual savings for all NHS providers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> can be delivered in a way that will not adversely and significantly impact on the safe and effective delivery of patient care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">articularly when the vast majority of p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">roviders, des</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">pite their best efforts, are now patently unable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">deliver </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the current requirement of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4% ann</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ual recurrent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">efficiency savings</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (see paras 3 to 7 of this submission)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">New models of working require investment and time to deliver, whereas ITF resources will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mmediately </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">be shifted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">directly from the NHS frontline – often from pressure points in the system</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> includ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing accident and emergency care.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Managing the risk from the ITF to NHS services</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">To date, the Government has declined requests to release </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">detailed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">terms of a tripartite m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inisterial agreement between DH, DCLG and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Treasury on the operation of the ITF</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">hampered</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the FTN’s ability, in its dialogue with DH, to help ensure that the risk to NHS services from the introduction of the ITF is appro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">priately managed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The FTN has a series of concerns about the ITF based on the early public documentation issued on the fund including:</span></li></ol><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he Government</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> intention to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">hold back performance-related fu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nding if goals are not achieved</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The failure to fully inv</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">olve providers in assessing and managing the risk to NHS services</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The asymmetry in the ITF national conditions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, wherein</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> CCGs and local authorities need to state how they will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">protect </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">so</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">cial care services</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">while </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">they only need to set out the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">consequences </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">for NHS services</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The assumption that the ITF</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> will adversely impact </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">only </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the acute sector, when it is likely that it will also adversely  affect </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">community, mental</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> health and ambulance providers</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Chief Executive of NHS England has described </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the ITF </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">a game changer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We hope it will change the game in a positive way</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> but believe the balance of probability is strongly loaded the other way in the short term: it is likely to bring major risk to effective NHS service delivery and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">patient care as it </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">divert</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s a significant amount of funding away from existing NHS service delivery</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">understand the policy intent, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but worry that the consequences for NHS services have not been fully </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">accounted for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">2014/15 National Tariff Payment System: A Consultation Notice (Monitor)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">McKinsey Hospital Institute</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">How is the health and social care system </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">performing?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> (Kings Fund)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">September 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> Sir David Nicholson letter to CCGs, 10 October, para</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> 5.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> HSJ, 18 July 2013</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">.</span></p></body></html>